text: The Deutsche Evangelisch Lutherische Zion Kirche, also known as Our Redeemer Lutheran Church of Marysville, is a historic church building in Staplehurst, Nebraska. It was built in 1917 "as the culmination of the fund-raising efforts of farmers in rural Seward County." With It was designed in the Late Gothic Revival style by George A. Berlinghof and Ellery L. Davis. It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since June 25, 1982. ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Seward County, Nebraska Category:Gothic Revival church buildings in Nebraska Category:Churches completed in 1917
